== Milestones - Making the game
Version < 1.0 (alpha)
(in alpha1) * Have a working Sprite editor + loader
---
(in alpha2) * Have a working level editor
(in alpha2) * Be able to load and save levels (in editor)
---
(in alpha3) * Be able to load levels (in game)
(in alpha3) * Be able to move the player around
(in alpha3) * Have a ball bouncing around
(in alpha3) * Have a ball bounce off the paddle and tiles (with angle)
(in alpha3) * Have a ball destroy tiles
---
(in alpha4) * Blocks take 2 hits to die (Start of block properties)
(in alpha4) * Win condition (all tiles destroyed)
(in alpha4) * Be able to lose balls to the bottom of the screen
(in alpha4) * Fail condition (3 balls lost)
(in alpha4) * Have a "Click To Start" message
(in alpha4) * Level Properties Editor
(in alpha4) * Fix all bugs found up to this point
---
(in alpha5) * interface to load levels (levels to chose from are .lvl files)
(in alpha5) * Beautify level loading interface
(in alpha5) * Add a way to pause the game
(in alpha5) * Add an "Are you sure you want to quit?" message
(in alpha5) * Go back to level loader when you beat or lose a level
---
(in alpha6) * Progressable levels (you start with level one, beat it, automatically move to level two)
(in alpha6) * Saved progression (you can continue on the level you left off on)
(in alpha6) * ESC while in-game should quit to main menu, ESC while in menu should exit the game
---
(in alpha7) * Bouncing Sound
(planned alpha7) * Upgrades when tiles are destroyed (bonus life, bigger paddle, etc.)
(planned alpha7) * Downgrades when tiles are destroyed (smaller paddle, faster ball, etc.)
---
(planned alpha8) * Options - Turn off fx, music, etc

Version 1.1 (beta)
* polish (better graphics, add effects, clean up code, address any bugs)

Version 1.2 (release)
* create at least 20 levels 

== Milestones - Game Made
* document code
* create a level making tutorial
